language.description: The two-letter ISO 639-1 language for which the status is reported.

errors.description: The list of errors occurring in the feed.

lastUploadDate.description: The last date at which the feed was uploaded.

country.description: The country for which the status is reported, represented as a CLDR territory code.

warnings.description: The list of errors occurring in the feed.

itemsValid.description: The number of items in the feed that were valid.

kind.description: Identifies what kind of resource this is. Value: the fixed string "`content#datafeedStatus`"

processingStatus.description: The processing status of the feed. Acceptable values are: - "`"`failure`": The feed could not be processed or all items had errors.`" - "`in progress`": The feed is being processed. - "`none`": The feed has not yet been processed. For example, a feed that has never been uploaded will have this processing status. - "`success`": The feed was processed successfully, though some items might have had errors.

DatafeedStatus.description: The status of a datafeed, i.e., the result of the last retrieval of the datafeed computed asynchronously when the feed processing is finished.
